    narr:generatedFrom "d1b09a828565de86" ;
    narr:narration """Pricing evolved through repeated reframing. [Feb per-repo pricing](narr:Claim_ThreeTierSupersedes) ([amount]/mo, 10 seats) gave way to a [March three-tier model](narr:Narrative_ThreeTierPricingModel) — Individual/Team/Professional — then a [four-tier structure](narr:Narrative_NewTierStructure_20260319) adding Free, then a [rename](narr:Narrative_TierRenameExpertTeam) (Individual→Expert, Publisher→Team), still unpropagated in code. By May 18 the structure [firmed](narr:Claim_OrgBaseLocked4K): Org [amount]/mo floor, Expert [amount]/user, Team [amount]/user (10 seats), plus value-priced [EDO add-ons](narr:Claim_EDO_SingleTenantManaged). The [10x Team→Professional gap](narr:Narrative_10xGapIsFeature) is positioned as intentional signal — a human doing work for you. Validation arrived from prospects: the customer's chief architect called [[amount]'not real money'](narr:Claim_400PerMonthNotRealMoney), Tony said the tiers [track for him](narr:Claim_PricingTierValidatedByTony), the customer's CTO probed [scaling and the team→enterprise switch](narr:Claim_CustomerCTOScalingPricing). The [setup fee was reframed](narr:Narrative_SetupFeeAsConversionService) as a conversion service, with [we-do-it vs they-do-it](narr:Claim_TheyDoItConversionModel) revenue splits. Competitive framing: aswritten [2-10x cheaper](narr:Claim_AswrittenCheaperThanTierB) than Tier B assembly.""" ;
